# Tauri / Rust
src-tauri/target/
src-tauri/gen/
# Cargo.lock IS committed (binary crate) so CI reproduces the exact
# dependency graph local validated. Don't re-gitignore without
# replacing with an alternative reproducibility mechanism — last
# uncommitted-lockfile incident: v0.7.55 CI failed when crates.io
# served time v0.3.48 (incompatible with tauri-utils 2.9.2 trait impls)
# while local had time v0.3.47.

